# Movie Finder Backend — Cursor Rules

You are working in the movie-finder-backend workspace.
Primary reference: CLAUDE.md (loaded automatically; also valid for Cursor).

## What this workspace does

FastAPI backend — HTTP/SSE API layer.
uv workspace: `app/` and `chain/` are members; `imdbapi/` and `rag_ingestion/` are path deps.

## All quality commands run inside Docker

```bash
make lint            # ruff check (report only)
make fix             # ruff --fix + format (auto-apply)
make typecheck       # mypy --strict
make test            # pytest app/tests/
make test-coverage   # pytest + reports/ (JUnit + Cobertura XML + htmlcov)
make pre-commit      # full pre-commit suite
```

## Python rules

- mypy --strict must pass — no type: ignore without explanatory comment
- No bare except: — catch specific types
- No print() — use logging
- Async all the way — never block in async context
- Line length: 100 (ruff)
- Docstrings on all public classes and functions (Google style)

## Design patterns (follow strictly)

- Dependency injection: FastAPI Depends() for db pool, auth, config, graph
- Repository: data access in repository classes — no raw SQL in route handlers
- Configuration: Pydantic BaseSettings — never os.getenv() in business logic
- Middleware: cross-cutting concerns in middleware
- SSE: thin proxy route — business logic stays in chain/

## Test outputs

All test outputs go to `reports/`:
- `reports/junit.xml`
- `reports/coverage.xml`
- `reports/htmlcov/`

## CI

Per-repo CI: Lint + Typecheck + Test only.
Image builds happen in the root movie-finder pipeline.
